Introduction

Lee Heeseung is a South Korean singer-songwriter, dancer, composer, and producer under HYBE Labels and Belift Lab. He is best known as the main vocalist and the oldest member of the boy group ENHYPEN.

On June 1, 2020, Heeseung was introduced as a contestant in the CJ ENM and Big Hit Entertainment's reality survival show I-LAND. On September 18, 2020, he ranked 5th place by global votes and became a member of the boy group ENHYPEN.

He made his debut as a member of ENHYPEN on November 30, 2020, with their first mini album "Border : Day One".
